        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2019-09-10 06:43:12.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI'm always a bit worried by this new kind of proposition (it goes also with nfs-provisionner, and maybe all the databases charts): it exists in the Helm / operator community stable and \"official\" charts /operators (https://github.com/helm/charts/tree/master/stable/prometheus-operator, https://github.com/helm/charts/tree/master/stable, https://github.com/helm/charts/tree/master/stable/nfs-client-provisioner, https://github.com/helm/charts/tree/master/stable/nfs-server-provisioner, https://github.com/helm/charts/tree/master/stable/mongodb-replicaset, https://hub.helm.sh/charts/bitnami/mariadb-galera, https://github.com/coreos/etcd-operator, https://github.com/Orange-OpenSource/cassandra-k8s-operator, ...).\nHaving them in OOM repository will need to stay in line with them.\nCouldn't we mark them (at least the one in stable helm) as requirements when needed instead of adding them into OOM?",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
